    {
        "content": "<p>Boolean algebra: <a href=\"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib/blob/master/src/order/boolean_algebra.lean\">https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib/blob/master/src/order/boolean_algebra.lean</a><br>\nOrdered comm monoid: <a href=\"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib/blob/master/src/algebra/ordered_group.lean\">https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib/blob/master/src/algebra/ordered_group.lean</a></p>",
        "id": 200808469,
        "sender_full_name": "Kenny Lau",
        "timestamp": 1592127231
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Currently a Boolean algebra is not a ring</p>",
        "id": 200808510,
        "sender_full_name": "Kenny Lau",
        "timestamp": 1592127255
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>what should we do about this?</p>",
        "id": 200808514,
        "sender_full_name": "Kenny Lau",
        "timestamp": 1592127260
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Sorry, <span class=\"user-mention\" data-user-id=\"110064\">@Kenny Lau</span>, could you be less telegraphic? I'm not sure what it is you're worried about.</p>",
        "id": 200810343,
        "sender_full_name": "Scott Morrison",
        "timestamp": 1592130497
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>sorry for not expressing myself clearly, I'm just wondering whether we should define a ring structure on a boolean algebra</p>",
        "id": 200810352,
        "sender_full_name": "Kenny Lau",
        "timestamp": 1592130536
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>and then prove that any Boolean algebra is an ordered comm monoid</p>",
        "id": 200810357,
        "sender_full_name": "Kenny Lau",
        "timestamp": 1592130548
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>as in <a href=\"http://math.mit.edu/~jerison/103/handouts/rings.pdf\">http://math.mit.edu/~jerison/103/handouts/rings.pdf</a></p>",
        "id": 200811226,
        "sender_full_name": "Scott Morrison",
        "timestamp": 1592132112
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I guess I don't know how useful it is to do this...?</p>",
        "id": 200811231,
        "sender_full_name": "Scott Morrison",
        "timestamp": 1592132128
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>well, ordered_comm_monoid was introduced 5 days ago in <a href=\"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib/issues/2844\">#2844</a> and I thought it would be useful to have some examples</p>",
        "id": 200811290,
        "sender_full_name": "Kenny Lau",
        "timestamp": 1592132225
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I just worry that allowing people to use <code>+</code> to mean \"symmetric difference of sets\" is unlikely to lead to clarity. :-)</p>",
        "id": 200811353,
        "sender_full_name": "Scott Morrison",
        "timestamp": 1592132321
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>But I guess if it's done with <code>def</code> and not <code>instance</code> it's fine for constructing examples.</p>",
        "id": 200811364,
        "sender_full_name": "Scott Morrison",
        "timestamp": 1592132348
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I think adding boolean rings is a fine idea. Maybe we could get <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Stone%27s_representation_theorem_for_Boolean_algebras\">Stone's representation theorem</a> too.</p>",
        "id": 200820771,
        "sender_full_name": "Bryan Gin-ge Chen",
        "timestamp": 1592148032
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Please don't add this as a ring instance on prop/set.</p>",
        "id": 200836998,
        "sender_full_name": "Yury G. Kudryashov",
        "timestamp": 1592174384
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>There are also times where you do want to have an additive or multiplicative structure on a lattice, which might conflict with a boolean_ring instance</p>",
        "id": 202400631,
        "sender_full_name": "Aaron Anderson",
        "timestamp": 1593499670
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I would be interested in working on an implementation of the Stone representation theorem though, just with a function that takes a boolean algebra lattice instance to a boolean ring ordered ring instance</p>",
        "id": 202400762,
        "sender_full_name": "Aaron Anderson",
        "timestamp": 1593499786
    }
]